Social media writer Kemi Olunloyo has advised those against the declaration of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed as president-elect.  She said those opposing a Yoruba man as President should have a rethink. Read Also : Oromroni: Falana asks police to investigate Kemi Olunloyo’s claim She said: “IGBO PEOPLE: Stop being bitter, power shifted to a Yoruba man. Work with him. Nothing wrong with being a tribalism. We have tribes. The ere are more Igbo kids born in Lagos and South West than in Igboland due to Biafra war and migration. One of them will be a Governor/ Prez one day.”